      indicator: [ { text: 'Indicator1' },
        { text: 'Indicator2' },
        { text: 'Indicator3' },
        { text: 'Indicator4' },
        { text: 'Indicator5' }],
      triggerEvent: true,
      axisName: {
        formatter(value: string) {
          if (value === 'Indicator4') {
            return '{active|' + value + '}'
          }
          return value
        },
        rich: {
          active: {
            color: '#238CE8'
          }
        }
      }
    },

### Current Behavior

When I dynamically modify an indicator in the radar chart, part of its content will also change and the rich text format will be retained.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57605894/199203842-0c8369a8-8598-49ee-9eeb-5512f67f6198.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57605894/199203894-aa5de1b5-3907-49df-9f14-2eae68cc43a8.png)


### Expected Behavior

I think in the right case the content should take out the part of the content recognized by the rich text

### Environment

```markdown
- OS:windows
- Browser:chrome
- Framework:vue@3
```


### Any additional comments?

I found one in the official example to try and have the same problem

