<details><summary><b>TRANSLATED</b></summary><br>

**TITLE**

[Bug] After the mobile phone chart executes the mouse event, the globalout event is not executed, how to solve this, version 5.1.2

**BODY**

### Version

5.1.2

### Link to Minimal Reproduction

_No response_

### Steps to Reproduce

`myChart.getZr().off('click');
     
        myChart.getZr().on('click', (events) => {
          const pointInPixel = [events.offsetX, events.offsetY];
          if (!myChart.containPixel('grid', pointInPixel)) {
            unTriggerTooltip();
          }
        });
       // After this is executed, the globalout event is not executed
        myChart.getZr().on('mousemove', (events) => {
          const pointInPixel = [events.offsetX, events.offsetY];
          if (!myChart.containPixel('grid', pointInPixel)) {
            unTriggerTooltip();
          }
        });

        myChart.getZr().on('globalout', () => {
          console.log('globalout');
          unTriggerTooltip();
        });`

### Current Behavior

On the mobile phone iOS, after the icon executes the click event, the data of the currently selected date is displayed, and the initial value is displayed by clicking on the area outside the chart, which is OK. However, when the chart triggers the finger sliding event to display the current date data, and then clicks outside the chart, the globalout event will not be executed.

### Expected Behavior

Select the chart or mouse chart to display the data of the corresponding date, click the area outside the chart to display the initial value

